The cure was devised by “a great physician.'’ But see Donne :—

When no physician of redress can speak, A joyful casual violence may break A dangerous aposthume in thy breast. “Anatomy, Second Ann.,” ll. 477-9.

Webster says of Prince Henry that

We stood as in some spacious theatre, Musing what would become of him, his flight Reach’d such a noble pitch above our sight, &c. “A Monumental Column,” 11. 48-50.

And he follows up this statement by a reference to an age of golden dreams. So in Donne :—

She, to whom all this world was but a stage, Where all sat hearkening how her youthful age Should be employ’d, because in all she did Some figure of the golden times was hid. “Anatorny‚ Second Ann.,'' ll. 67-70.
